{"questionId":"22642082","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Diego is a teacher in the school. He believes that the number of students, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, who have had influenza during the first&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> days of the school year, can be modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>headlice.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>42</mn><mn>500</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>21</mn><mn>250</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>084</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award<em><strong> A1 </strong></em>for numerator, <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for denominator.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22642082","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.1ci","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"headlice.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
